  "title": "Google analytics",
  "content": "\nElement load analytics for tracking particular variants of a page or feature.\nTo add analytics, add a data-ga-load attribute to an element. The value\nshould be a comma-separated list of the with the GA Category, Action, Label,\nand Value (optional).\n&lt;a href=\"/signup\" data-ga-load=\"Dashboard, view, sparkly octocat banner\"&gt;signup&lt;/a&gt;\n\nRecord custom events generated by the server. See data-ga-load for values.\n&lt;meta name=\"analytics-event\" content=\"Signup, Success, Homepage Form\"&gt;\n\nGeneral click-tracking for DOM elements. See data-ga-load for values.\n&lt;a href=\"/signup\" data-ga-click=\"Signup, click, homepage banner\"&gt;signup&lt;/a&gt;\n\n",
